import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    plt.hist(data['delay'], bins=20, edgecolor='black')
    plt.xlabel('Delay')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of flight delays?')
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    plt.scatter(data['distance'], data['delay'])
    plt.xlabel('Distance')
    plt.ylabel('Delay')
    plt.title('What is the relationship between distance and delay?')
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    
    origin_counts = data['origin'].value_counts()
    destination_counts = data['destination'].value_counts()
    
    combined_counts = pd.concat([origin_counts, destination_counts], axis=1)
    combined_counts.columns = ['Origin', 'Destination']
    
    ax = combined_counts.plot(kind='bar', rot=45)
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        ax.xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    plt.title("What is the most common origin and destination for flights?")
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='ignore')
    flight_counts = data['date'].value_counts().sort_index()
    
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    plt.plot(flight_counts.index, flight_counts.values)
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    
    plt.title("What is the distribution of flight dates?", wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    
    avg_delay_by_origin = data.groupby('origin')['delay'].mean()
    avg_delay_by_origin.plot(kind='bar')
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.title("What is the average delay time for each origin airport?", wrap=True)
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()
